# 📡 SUPERSPLOIT SESSION MANAGER
The Session Manager handles active C2 connections, providing a robust interface for interacting with remote agents via an encrypted, in-memory pipeline.

---

## 🚀 "UNDER THE HOOD" MECHANISMS
- Secure TLS Stream: All session traffic is encapsulated in a 4096-bit RSA TLS stream. The framework auto-generates ephemeral self-signed certificates (c2_cert.pem) on startup.
- Interactive QOL: Interaction sessions feature persistent command history (`c2_history`), auto-suggestions, command chaining (`&&`), local output redirection (`>`), and local command piping (`|`).
- Crypto-Layer (XOR/B64): Data within the TLS stream is further obfuscated using a user-defined XOR_KEY and Base64 encoding.
- Heartbeat & Jitter: The listener sends 0-length "Keepalive" frames with randomized jitter (45-75s) to maintain persistence.
- Stage 2 Deployment: Initial connections trigger the in-memory deployment of a zlib-compressed, encrypted Stage 2 Python payload.
- Automated Enrichment: If AUTO_ENUM is enabled (default: true), the listener automatically deploys the Version 5.0 "Ultra-Enum" suite on new Android sessions to map the LPE surface and enrich the target profile with "micro-crack" research.

---

## 🛠️ COMMAND SYNTAX & FLAGS
### sessions
Lists all active background sessions with their IDs, Peer addresses, and status.

### sessions -i <ID>
Interact with a specific session. Drops you into the C2 Interaction Menu.

### sessions -k <ID> / sessions -K
Kill a specific session or terminate all active sessions.

